    "reasoning": "First, determine the polynomial P(x) from P(10)=331633 and P(-10)=273373 with coefficients nonnegative integers less than 100. By considering the sum and difference, we find the even and odd parts: P(10)+P(-10)=605006 gives a0+100a2+10000a4+...=302503, which in base 100 yields a0=3, a2=25, a4=30, and other even coefficients 0. P(10)-P(-10)=58260 gives 10a1+1000a3+...=29130, so a1+100a3+...=2913, yielding a1=13, a3=29, a5=0. Thus P(x)=3+13x+25x^2+29x^3+30x^4. Then a3=29, so k=a3-27=2.\n\nNext, for a right triangle with relatively prime integer side lengths (primitive Pythagorean triple), parameterize as a=m^2-n^2, b=2mn, c=m^2+n^2 with m>n>0, gcd(m,n)=1, and opposite parity. Then perimeter P=2m(m+n), area A=mn(m^2-n^2). Compute (P^2)/A=4m(m+n)/(n(m-n)). For this to be an integer, note gcd(n,m-n)=1 and gcd(n,m+n)=1, so n must divide 4. Thus n∈{1,2,4}. Check each: n=1 gives integer only for m=2, yielding 24; n=2 gives integer only for m=3, yielding 30; n=4 gives integer only for m=5, yielding 45. The largest integer is 45.",
